title: Being serious about pleasure feels good.
pid: 64e86cbe-bfb9-489b-82e6-33a73f572415
body: |2-
  Fake smiles devalue real ones, but it's not just that.
  The time spent not smiling can also feel good.
  Seriousness, maybe heaviness, focus, certainty, familiarity
  -- they come together in
  an alternate, equally (? valid, good) cognitive state.
misc:
- Had_ID_Before_Import
